CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 4, 1958, pg. A6 reads: "That Holiday Spirit - The friends of Timmie Williams of 3300 Iowa St. gathered to exercise that holiday spirit at a party Dec. 27. Dancing to the music of Tim's "neat" hi-fi were, left to right, kneeling: Charles Hampton, Turner Green and Reginald Roach.  Seated: Barbara Mills, Carole VeLar, Donna Rideout, Bernice VeLar, Antoinette McTurner, Norma Pedigrew, Sarah Burney and Leo Turner.  Standing: William Harris, Ronald Talbert, Joseph Herd, Wynn Jones, Roger Thomas, Carl Dorsey, Tim Williams, Betty Ferguson, Barbara Brooks and David Carmichael. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of birthday party participants, from left, kneeling: Charles Hampton, Turner Green, and Reginald Roach; seated: Barbara Mills, Carole VeLar, Donna Rideout, Bernice VeLar, Antoinette McTurner, Norma Pedigrew, Sarah Burney, and Leo Turner; standing: William Harris, Ronald Talbert, Joseph Herd, Wynn Jones, Roger Thomas, Carl Dorsey, Tim Williams, guest of honor; Betty Ferguson, Barbara Brooks, and David Carmichael, posed in Tim Williams home, 3300 Iowa Street
